{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015GzAPQQiUVJ3DcUNk8kWsX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All jobs are done. Here's a summary of what was done and the results:\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\n### Diagnosis\nThe deployment was structurally correct — the Spark master/worker cluster came up cleanly and the baseline job ran successfully using `--master local[2]` (local Spark mode). No configuration fixes were needed beyond what the precondition already applied.\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | Optimization | Benefit |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Baseline** | 24.59s | None | Skewed shuffle join (10x partition imbalance) |\n| **Broadcast Join** | 12.39s | `broadcast_join` | No shuffle, no skew — 2x faster |\n| **AQE** | 13.49s | `aqe_skew_join` | Auto-splits hot partitions — 1.8x faster |\n\n### How each optimization helps\n\n- **Broadcast Join**: The small `products` table (100 rows) is broadcast to all executors, eliminating the shuffle entirely. Hot product_id keys (1–5) no longer cause straggler partitions.\n- **AQE (Adaptive Query Execution)**: Spark detects skewed partitions at runtime and automatically splits them into smaller sub-tasks, distributing work more evenly.\n\nBoth strategies reduced runtime from ~24.6s to ~12–13s (~2x speedup) by avoiding the root cause: a hash-partitioned shuffle where 50% of orders land on 5 product_id keys."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":517,"cache_read_input_tokens":52297,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":517},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"126e4225-41eb-4ea9-828c-4b3d216dfc50","uuid":"df51280b-1c4d-4ee2-bc37-efac4c3f2964","request_id":"req_011Cc7pEu2BJoqsikEpRWqu5"}
